Boris Ivanovich Gostev (Russian:   ; 15 September 1927  10 August 2015) was a Soviet engineer, economist and politician.

== Biography ==
Gostev was born in 1927. He served as aide to Prime Minister Nikolai Ryzhkov. Gostev was appointed minister of finance on 14 December 1985, replacing long-term finance minister Vasily F. Garbuzov in the post. Gostev's term ended on 17 July 1989. He died in 2015.

